WEBVTT

00:01.794 --> 00:05.089
NARRATOR:
In a land of myth and a time of magic,

00:05.173 --> 00:09.844
the destiny of a great kingdom
rests on the shoulders of a young boy.

00:10.428 --> 00:12.930
His name, Merlin.

00:30.531 --> 00:32.825
(HAMMERING)

00:48.007 --> 00:49.967
(COUGHING)

01:11.989 --> 01:13.491
(EXHALING)

01:14.492 --> 01:16.494
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

01:17.119 --> 01:18.996
Merlin.

01:22.083 --> 01:23.292
Merlin!

01:25.086 --> 01:26.254
Yes, sire?

01:26.337 --> 01:27.380
Are you deaf?

01:29.048 --> 01:30.091
| wish.

01:30.841 --> 01:33.469
| want you to go down there
and tell them to stop.

01:33.928 --> 01:35.429
But they're working under
the King's orders.

01:35.721 --> 01:38.849
Yeah. And you're working under mine.

01:41.519 --> 01:42.853
(SIGHING)

02:00.746 --> 02:02.957
(INDISTINCT WHISPERING)

02:05.084 --> 02:06.961
(WHIP LASHING)

02:07.044 --> 02:08.461
(LOUD THUD)

02:13.259 --> 02:15.219
(MEN SCREAMING)

02:39.035 --> 02:41.203
(INDISTINCT WHISPERING)

02:54.717 --> 02:56.010
Hello.

03:39.970 --> 03:42.139
How do you think he died?

03:43.557 --> 03:44.725
Gaius?

03:44.809 --> 03:45.935
Hmm.

03:46.143 --> 03:47.812
(INDISTINCT WHISPERING)

03:50.940 --> 03:53.234
Do you know whose tomb it is?

03:53.401 --> 03:54.902
I'm not sure.

03:56.737 --> 03:58.406
Do you think it might be cursed?

04:03.452 --> 04:04.787
(RUMBLING)

04:04.870 --> 04:06.288
(WHOOSHING)

04:09.041 --> 04:10.292
(GASPS)

04:12.002 --> 04:13.504
You've just saved my life.

04:14.964 --> 04:16.673
-UTHER: Get out of my way.
-Thank you.

04:16.757 --> 04:18.843
UTHER: Make sure the entrance
is guarded at all times.

04:22.471 --> 04:23.681
Idiot.

04:25.141 --> 04:27.143
Were you born clumsy
or do you work at it?

04:27.601 --> 04:29.353
It's just one of my many gifts.

04:30.020 --> 04:33.691
Well, this is quite a find.
You see, Gaius. I was right.

04:34.567 --> 04:36.861
There is treasure to be found
under Camelot.

04:39.280 --> 04:42.116
Which of my predecessors
do I have to thank for all this?

04:44.452 --> 04:47.163
-Gaiusâ€?
-I would have to look into it, sire.

04:52.126 --> 04:53.461
UTHER: How did he die?

04:53.544 --> 04:56.589
He seems to have unwittingly
triggered a trap. Here.

04:56.881 --> 04:58.090
To deter grave robbers.

04:58.174 --> 05:00.676
There's plenty in here
people would want to steal.

05:02.011 --> 05:04.972
Have them secure the tomb. Guarding it
is your responsibility, Arthur.

05:05.723 --> 05:06.974
Yes, father.

05:14.273 --> 05:17.943
So this jewel...
What size would you say it was?

05:19.195 --> 05:20.279
About that size.

05:20.362 --> 05:22.948
My word. Really?
About that size, you say.

05:23.824 --> 05:25.409
Here you are, drink up.

05:26.452 --> 05:27.995
And this tomb...

05:28.954 --> 05:31.373
| bet they've got that locked up,
nice and safe, haven't they?

05:31.457 --> 05:33.626
-Tighter than the King's coffers.
-Yeah.

05:34.293 --> 05:35.794
There must be a way in though?

05:36.629 --> 05:38.005
Only with the keys.

05:38.589 --> 05:42.009
Right, right, right.
And who's got the keys?

05:44.094 --> 05:47.765
You must think I'm stupid.
I'm not telling you that.

05:48.098 --> 05:49.517
Course not.

05:49.600 --> 05:53.229
A bright lad like you knows what that
sort of information is worth.

05:55.105 --> 05:57.024
We don't want everyone to see.

05:57.942 --> 06:01.028
Believe me, this place is full
of thieves and fingersmiths.

06:01.111 --> 06:02.905
Put it inside your tunic.

06:04.156 --> 06:06.575
And careful of that fellow over there.

06:07.368 --> 06:08.744
Which one?

06:09.370 --> 06:13.290
Far end of the bar, do you see him?
He keeps on watching you.

06:13.374 --> 06:15.709
Yeah, yeah, yeah, with the beard.

06:16.502 --> 06:18.837
No, that one.

06:22.258 --> 06:24.468
| got my eye on him.

06:25.094 --> 06:26.178
Thank you.

06:27.388 --> 06:28.806
So who's got the keys?

06:31.642 --> 06:32.851
Only the prince.

06:34.353 --> 06:36.438
But don't get your hopes up.

06:36.522 --> 06:38.482
He keeps them
in his private chambers.

06:38.983 --> 06:43.696
And there's only one person
allowed in there, his servant.

06:44.238 --> 06:46.365
-ARTHUR: Hurry up, Merlin.
-Sorry.

06:56.709 --> 06:58.085
(GRUNTING)

07:02.840 --> 07:04.216
Merlin!

07:04.883 --> 07:07.553
-I don't understand.
-Well there's a surprise.

07:07.678 --> 07:10.681
- I did that girth up myself.
-That might have been the problem.

07:11.473 --> 07:12.683
It wasn't my fault!

07:12.766 --> 07:15.519
Would you like me to fit the girth
properly for you, sire?

07:17.688 --> 07:19.064
Thank you.

07:19.148 --> 07:21.525
It is an honor to be of service
to the Prince.

07:22.776 --> 07:25.321
An honor. Do you hear that, Merlin?

07:25.404 --> 07:28.449
Allow me the honor
of brushing your clothes down?

07:32.953 --> 07:34.622
(MOUTHING)
"The honor."

07:35.039 --> 07:37.041
Anything else I can do for you, sire?

07:37.875 --> 07:40.419
You can give Merlin here
a kick up the backside.

07:40.794 --> 07:42.212
(CHUCKLING)

07:42.296 --> 07:44.673
| wouldn't wish to deprive you
of the pleasure, sir.

07:45.507 --> 07:47.635
What's your name?

07:47.926 --> 07:49.094
Cedric.

07:49.178 --> 07:51.180
I've come to Camelot in search of work.

07:51.639 --> 07:53.682
Good, you can be a beater on the hunt,

07:53.766 --> 07:55.434
we're short of a man or two.

07:56.060 --> 07:57.728
You are too kind, sire.

07:59.813 --> 08:02.399
Here, you'll need a beater.

08:02.566 --> 08:04.151
Oh, sorry.

08:22.044 --> 08:23.754
(DOOR OPENING)

08:30.761 --> 08:32.929
(INDISTINCT WHISPERING)

09:11.343 --> 09:12.928
(BOAR GRUNTING)

09:23.230 --> 09:24.773
(ROARING)

09:24.857 --> 09:26.150
(GASPING)

09:44.710 --> 09:46.128
(CHANTING)

09:48.881 --> 09:50.799
(SQUEALING)

09:52.718 --> 09:54.678
(PANTING)

09:56.722 --> 09:58.265
(EXHALES)

10:02.478 --> 10:03.854
Who threw that?

10:10.944 --> 10:12.279
(PANTING)

10:14.239 --> 10:15.949
(CLEARING THROAT)

10:16.658 --> 10:18.076
Was it you?

10:21.121 --> 10:22.372
You just saved my life!

10:23.248 --> 10:25.626
Honestly, sire, it was nothing.

10:26.794 --> 10:29.838
| shall be forever indebted to you.
You must be rewarded.

10:29.922 --> 10:31.423
No. I couldn't possibly...

10:32.549 --> 10:34.885
Come on! What do you wish for?

10:35.719 --> 10:38.222
-I desire only one thing, sire.
-Anything.

10:39.556 --> 10:41.433
-A position in the Royal Household.
-Good.

10:42.726 --> 10:43.894
Consider it done.

10:47.147 --> 10:49.024
You can have that back now.

10:49.107 --> 10:50.943
Oh, sorry.

11:13.257 --> 11:14.383
What's wrong?

11:14.466 --> 11:17.886
| saved Arthur's life,
someone else got the credit.

11:17.970 --> 11:20.681
Just the usual. What're you doing?

11:22.349 --> 11:24.685
| found this inscription on the scepter.

11:27.312 --> 11:30.107
-What language is that?
- I don't know.

11:30.357 --> 11:32.901
Sigan would have known
many languages.

11:32.985 --> 11:35.028
-Sigan?
-It's his tomb.

11:35.821 --> 11:37.531
Who was he?

11:37.823 --> 11:41.952
Merlin, he was the most powerful
sorcerer to have lived.

11:42.452 --> 11:44.955
-Really?
-You didn't grow up in Camelot.

11:45.038 --> 11:47.040
But for those of us that did,

11:47.124 --> 11:50.711
Cornelius Sigan
was a figure of nightmare.

11:51.336 --> 11:52.671
Why?

11:53.714 --> 11:55.465
Sigan's powers.

11:56.133 --> 11:59.761
He could change day into night,
turn the tides.

11:59.845 --> 12:04.725
And, legend has it,
his spells helped build Camelot itself.

12:06.977 --> 12:08.186
What happened?

12:08.312 --> 12:09.688
In the end he grew too powerful

12:09.813 --> 12:12.190
and the King at that time
ordered his execution.

12:15.652 --> 12:17.404
If he's dead, why are you so worried?

12:18.989 --> 12:20.157
Sigan couldn't bear the thought

12:20.240 --> 12:22.242
that his wealth and power
would die with him

12:22.326 --> 12:24.953
sO he became obsessed

12:25.037 --> 12:27.414
with finding a way
to defeat death itself.

12:28.498 --> 12:30.042
And do you think
he might have succeeded?

12:32.169 --> 12:35.172
Let's hope not, for all our sakes.

12:42.012 --> 12:44.431
Gaius. What is it you want?

12:45.515 --> 12:48.268
To seal up the burial chamber
and all its contents.

12:49.102 --> 12:50.604
Don't be ridiculous.

12:50.687 --> 12:54.942
The insignia on this ring
belongs to Cornelius Sigan.

12:56.526 --> 12:58.528
| believe it to be his tomb.

12:59.738 --> 13:03.033
In the old religion the name Sigan
means "Raven."

13:03.867 --> 13:05.243
No wonder the riches are so great.

13:05.535 --> 13:07.371
Then you are aware of the legend?

13:07.454 --> 13:09.081
Yes.

13:09.206 --> 13:12.125
I've always enjoyed the tale of
the arrogant sorcerer

13:12.209 --> 13:13.961
who came to an untimely end.

13:14.419 --> 13:17.881
According to the story,
Sigan cursed Camelot.

13:17.965 --> 13:21.051
He said he would one day return
and raze the city to the ground.

13:22.302 --> 13:25.305
Gaius, you've always my ally
in the war against sorcery.

13:25.389 --> 13:27.474
You, more than anyone,
should not give in

13:27.557 --> 13:29.893
to these irrational fears.

13:31.770 --> 13:33.438
Thank you, sire.

13:34.272 --> 13:38.402
And Gaius, do not spread panic
amongst my people.

13:39.736 --> 13:42.447
This is foolish superstition,
nothing more.

13:55.961 --> 13:57.421
(GASPING)

14:03.760 --> 14:05.053
(CAWING)

14:05.137 --> 14:06.513
(SCREAMS)

14:08.181 --> 14:10.517
Gwen. Gwen!

14:10.600 --> 14:12.769
My lady. My lady. What's the matter?

14:12.853 --> 14:15.313
GWEN: It's alright.
It's alright. I'm here.

14:15.439 --> 14:17.190
There's nothing to be frightened of.

14:17.649 --> 14:19.276
(SHUSHING)

14:28.535 --> 14:31.121
-ARTHUR: Is that lunch?
-No, it's breakfast...

14:34.458 --> 14:36.293
This is lovely, Cedric.

14:38.462 --> 14:41.298
Is there anything else
that you need doing, sire?

14:42.340 --> 14:43.967
No, I think Cedric's got it all covered.

14:46.136 --> 14:50.515
Oh! I regret, sire, there is
one thing I've failed to do.

14:50.807 --> 14:52.684
Muck out your horses.

14:56.146 --> 14:57.689
Off you go.

15:01.485 --> 15:03.403
I'll get the door for you.

15:24.758 --> 15:27.552
-What was this dream about?
-A bird.

15:30.222 --> 15:33.016
-What kind of bird?
-A raven.

15:33.100 --> 15:34.601
A raven?

15:35.268 --> 15:37.354
It was terrifying, Gaius.

15:38.855 --> 15:40.190
What do you think it means?

15:41.566 --> 15:43.110
Probably nothing.

15:43.860 --> 15:45.654
It's happening again, isn't it?

15:45.737 --> 15:50.575
Morgana, one raven doesn't mean
that your nightmares are returning.

15:53.453 --> 15:56.373
Are you taking the sleeping
draughts I prepared for you?

15:58.291 --> 16:01.086
I'll get Gwen to give you
something stronger.

16:01.753 --> 16:03.130
Like a blow to the head?

16:05.257 --> 16:06.883
I'm sure she wants to.

16:29.072 --> 16:30.907
(HORSES NEIGHING)

16:32.742 --> 16:36.454
Go on. Go and have some fun. Go on.

16:43.461 --> 16:44.754
Sire!

16:57.309 --> 16:59.436
(SNORING)

17:15.242 --> 17:17.621
-Sire!
-What are you doing?

17:20.290 --> 17:21.499
Nothing.

17:21.625 --> 17:22.791
| can see that.

17:25.127 --> 17:26.171
| wasn't sleeping.

17:27.255 --> 17:28.506
| was...

17:30.967 --> 17:32.302
| was just bending down.

17:32.802 --> 17:34.012
Looking for something?

17:34.638 --> 17:35.764
Yes.

17:36.181 --> 17:37.724
Perhaps we're looking
for the same thing.

17:37.807 --> 17:41.311
-What?
-I don't know...the horses?

17:41.686 --> 17:44.814
The horses? Oh!

17:44.940 --> 17:47.817
One mistake I can understand,
everyone has a bad day now and then,

17:47.943 --> 17:50.445
but this is one thing after another!

17:51.821 --> 17:53.823
| don't know what happened.

17:54.157 --> 17:55.367
Sire...

17:56.618 --> 17:58.161
Please, sire. Don't be too hard on him.

17:58.286 --> 18:00.747
He's a good servant, he's just tired.

18:00.830 --> 18:01.957
| am not!

18:02.040 --> 18:05.168
Maybe if he had the evening off.

18:05.293 --> 18:07.420
-I don't want the evening off.
-A good night's rest...

18:07.504 --> 18:09.005
| did not fall asleep!

18:09.214 --> 18:12.008
| am more than willing to
take over his duties tonight.

18:12.133 --> 18:14.010
-Perhaps you're right. Shut up, Merlin.
-No!

18:14.135 --> 18:16.554
Can't you see what he's trying to do?
He's trying to get rid of me!

18:16.680 --> 18:19.015
If you weren't such
a clotpole you'd see that.

18:19.182 --> 18:20.392
A what?

18:22.519 --> 18:24.813
Clotpole. He said clotpole.

18:29.651 --> 18:32.487
Cedric's right.
He can look after me tonight.

18:33.488 --> 18:35.532
You can go home

18:35.657 --> 18:37.826
and think about whether you
want to be my servant or not.

18:37.909 --> 18:39.536
-But...
-Go!

18:49.754 --> 18:51.381
(SIGHING)

19:03.768 --> 19:06.396
-What's that on your face?
-Nothing.

19:08.565 --> 19:10.400
-What's wrong?
-Nothing.

19:24.748 --> 19:26.249
Here.

19:32.255 --> 19:33.590
| am not an idiot.

19:34.257 --> 19:35.592
What happened?

19:38.386 --> 19:40.764
| just want Arthur to trust me

19:40.889 --> 19:42.432
and to see me for
who I really am.

19:43.641 --> 19:45.101
One day he will.

19:45.643 --> 19:46.770
When?

19:47.562 --> 19:50.148
Everything I do is for him and
he just thinks I'm an idiot.

19:51.983 --> 19:54.277
Not everyone thinks you're an idiot.

19:55.445 --> 19:58.156
Although looking at you now...

20:04.287 --> 20:07.499
Now is not the time to be
questioning these things, Merlin...

20:07.624 --> 20:10.710
| believe that you and Arthur
are destined for greatness.

20:10.794 --> 20:14.297
And that your calling is
to serve and protect him.

20:15.799 --> 20:18.134
-It's hard.
-I know it's hard,

20:18.843 --> 20:20.929
but Camelot is in grave peril.

20:21.012 --> 20:22.597
I've translated the inscription.

20:23.098 --> 20:27.310
"He who breaks my heart,
completes my work."

20:28.978 --> 20:30.271
What does it mean?

20:30.355 --> 20:32.524
You remember the stone in the tomb.
How it glowed?

20:32.816 --> 20:34.651
Yeah. I've never seen a jewel like it.

20:34.776 --> 20:36.945
That's because it's not a jewel.

20:37.028 --> 20:40.156
It's the soul of Cornelius Sigan.

20:41.658 --> 20:43.993
-You think he's alive?
-His soul is.

20:44.828 --> 20:47.747
But in order to truly live,
a soul needs a body.

20:47.831 --> 20:52.127
So if the stone
is removed from its setting,

20:53.503 --> 20:55.588
then the heart is broken
and the soul released.

20:55.672 --> 20:57.006
That's what I fear.

21:09.018 --> 21:11.688
I'll be right outside in the ante room
should you need me.

21:12.230 --> 21:14.315
That will be all, Cedric.

21:29.080 --> 21:30.832
Sleep well, sire.

21:44.429 --> 21:46.431
(INDISTINCT WHISPERING)

21:56.107 --> 21:57.567
Oh, yes.

21:58.568 --> 22:00.069
Oh, yes.

22:01.738 --> 22:03.114
Oh, yes.

22:05.575 --> 22:06.868
Oh, yes.

22:16.419 --> 22:17.754
(GASPING)

22:18.296 --> 22:19.881
Hello, ladies.

22:31.142 --> 22:32.477
(GASPING)

22:36.231 --> 22:38.483
(INDISTINCT WHISPERING)

22:38.983 --> 22:40.318
(GASPING)

22:53.248 --> 22:55.291
(GRUNTING)

22:57.418 --> 22:58.962
(CHUCKLING)

23:27.615 --> 23:29.242
(RAVEN CAWING)

23:47.635 --> 23:49.137
Sound the warning bell.

23:50.597 --> 23:52.098
Merlin?

23:54.934 --> 23:57.687
Whoever did this got more than
they bargained for.

23:59.439 --> 24:01.524
| don't understand how they got in.

24:03.276 --> 24:04.485
The gate's not even damaged.

24:04.777 --> 24:06.029
Must have used a key.

24:06.529 --> 24:07.697
Arthur's got the only key.

24:08.197 --> 24:09.490
Where does he keep it?

24:09.866 --> 24:11.034
On his belt with the others.

24:11.117 --> 24:12.535
GAUIS:
Does he ever take it off?

24:12.619 --> 24:14.704
Only when he's asleep.
He keeps it next to his bed.

24:16.205 --> 24:18.124
Who had access
to his chambers last night?

24:18.207 --> 24:19.792
Just me and...

24:23.504 --> 24:24.714
Cedric!

24:34.557 --> 24:38.728
Cedric is possessed by an evil spirit.

24:40.188 --> 24:41.564
What?

24:41.689 --> 24:44.484
He tried to steal the jewel.
But it wasn't a jewel.

24:44.567 --> 24:46.986
It was the soul
of an ancient sorcerer, Sigan.

24:48.154 --> 24:50.323
Merlin, have you been on the cider?

24:50.406 --> 24:52.659
Please. Listen to me,

24:54.077 --> 24:55.912
Camelot is in mortal danger.

24:56.496 --> 24:59.082
Sigan is using Cedric's body
to take his revenge.

24:59.207 --> 25:01.084
This nonsense isn't helping
you keep your job.

25:01.209 --> 25:02.710
You are not listening to me!

25:03.086 --> 25:05.004
If you're going to shout anyway.

25:05.088 --> 25:06.589
Cedric!

25:08.257 --> 25:11.010
Will you escort Merlin from the palace?

25:14.764 --> 25:16.349
(GRUNTING)

25:21.562 --> 25:23.690
(BOTH YELLING)

25:26.609 --> 25:27.860
Merlin!

25:48.923 --> 25:50.550
You've gone too far this time, Merlin.

25:50.633 --> 25:53.803
You can spend a few days
cooling off in the cells. Guards!

26:04.647 --> 26:07.150
He's going to destroy Camelot!

26:12.071 --> 26:13.740
(RAVEN CAWING)

26:24.417 --> 26:27.128
| am returned...

26:31.340 --> 26:34.927
(SPEAKING ANCIENT DIALECT)

26:36.846 --> 26:38.514
(CREATURE ROARING)

27:05.333 --> 27:06.709
(ROARING)

27:14.133 --> 27:15.301
(GASPING)

27:26.395 --> 27:28.564
| want to know what this creature is,
where it's come from.

27:28.689 --> 27:30.983
There is more than one, father.
We've had several.

27:31.067 --> 27:33.486
There's panic,
people are fleeing the city.

27:33.569 --> 27:35.822
Then you must hunt these
creatures down and kill them.

27:35.988 --> 27:37.240
Yes, sire.

27:38.533 --> 27:40.743
(ALL SCREAMING)

27:58.928 --> 28:00.555
(CREATURE GROWLING)

28:01.889 --> 28:03.057
(WOMAN SCREAMING)

28:06.602 --> 28:07.854
(GASPING)

28:10.398 --> 28:12.942
-Have you seen what is happening?
-It's as I warned you, sire.

28:13.067 --> 28:15.278
-This cannot be Sigan.
-It is his revenge.

28:15.361 --> 28:17.989
-He came back from the dead.
-He will die again.

28:18.072 --> 28:21.158
You cannot kill a man
who has conquered mortality.

28:21.242 --> 28:22.869
Don't tell me what cannot be done.

28:22.952 --> 28:25.288
Camelot will not fall to
a sorcerer while I am king.

28:47.894 --> 28:49.353
Hello!

28:58.112 --> 28:59.947
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

29:00.197 --> 29:03.159
Regroup! Form a phalanx!

29:13.586 --> 29:15.421
We need more bandages, Gwen.

29:18.007 --> 29:19.300
You shouldn't be doing this.

29:19.383 --> 29:21.469
It's exactly what I should be doing.

29:22.053 --> 29:23.471
You need rest, Morgana.

29:23.596 --> 29:25.681
And I'm likely to get it
with all this going on?

29:25.973 --> 29:27.433
(ROARING)

29:27.516 --> 29:28.851
(GRUNTING)

29:29.226 --> 29:31.312
(CREATURE SQUEALING)

29:42.531 --> 29:44.075
(CHANTING)

29:56.087 --> 29:57.838
-Guinevere!
-Sire.

29:59.090 --> 30:00.800
That thing could've killed you.

30:01.676 --> 30:03.427
And it still might.

30:05.680 --> 30:09.016
-Sorry, sire.
-No, my pleasure.

30:13.646 --> 30:15.439
(ROARING)

30:24.198 --> 30:26.409
I'll get you something
to stop the bleeding.

30:27.785 --> 30:29.412
Guinevere!

30:31.580 --> 30:33.791
| wanted to say...

30:36.961 --> 30:38.796
Just...

30:40.256 --> 30:42.466
You always surprise me.

30:46.012 --> 30:48.305
-Is that it, sire?
-That's it.

30:49.849 --> 30:51.809
Oh, and...

30:54.395 --> 30:55.730
Thank you.

31:05.156 --> 31:06.907
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

31:17.543 --> 31:18.836
UTHER: Arthur?

31:19.712 --> 31:21.047
It's nothing.

31:22.590 --> 31:23.883
Have we driven the creatures out?

31:23.966 --> 31:25.801
They have control of the lower town.

31:26.343 --> 31:28.220
The market has been all but destroyed.

31:28.304 --> 31:31.223
-How many dead?
-Too many to number.

31:31.849 --> 31:34.185
-I'm sealing the citadel.
-You can't.

31:34.268 --> 31:36.729
-I have no choice.
-(CREATURE GROWLING)

31:36.812 --> 31:38.981
| have to protect those
who have a chance.

31:39.065 --> 31:41.358
-If I don't, we will all fall.
-(LOUD THUDDING)

31:42.443 --> 31:43.527
Where are you going?

31:43.611 --> 31:45.529
There are people trapped
in the drawbridge.

31:45.613 --> 31:47.782
- I forbid you.
-I'm not leaving them to die.

31:48.074 --> 31:51.035
-It's suicide.
-It's my duty to Camelot

31:51.285 --> 31:52.787
and to myself.

32:04.715 --> 32:06.467
Gaius!

32:10.387 --> 32:11.847
What are you doing here?

32:11.931 --> 32:13.057
| have to help Arthur.

32:13.808 --> 32:17.353
-Sigan's power is far beyond yours.
- I don't have a choice.

32:17.436 --> 32:20.898
Sigan is immortal and you are not.
If you face him, he will destroy you.

32:20.981 --> 32:22.441
There must be a way.

32:24.819 --> 32:27.905
There is only one alive who can
give us the answers we need.

32:28.948 --> 32:30.157
What do you mean?

32:30.783 --> 32:32.076
(SIGHING)

32:32.785 --> 32:34.245
The Great Dragon.

32:39.625 --> 32:42.795
You knew, then...
That I used to visit him?

32:43.087 --> 32:45.131
Yes, Merlin. Of course I knew.

32:45.214 --> 32:47.716
You're a creature of magic
just as he is.

32:47.800 --> 32:49.176
| hoped that he could help you.

32:49.260 --> 32:51.428
He helps no-one but himself.

32:51.512 --> 32:53.597
For Arthur's sake,
you must go to him now.

32:53.681 --> 32:55.766
-I can't.
-We have no choice.

33:13.868 --> 33:15.411
Check for survivors.

33:16.162 --> 33:18.164
(CREATURE GROWLING)

33:20.541 --> 33:22.126
On me!

33:22.877 --> 33:24.128
(GROWLING)

33:24.420 --> 33:25.671
Charge!

33:37.224 --> 33:38.767
Hello?

33:43.189 --> 33:45.191
Hello?

33:49.653 --> 33:51.655
Please, I need your help.

33:54.783 --> 33:56.577
(CHAINS CLINKING)

33:59.121 --> 34:02.625
You told me I would not see you again.

34:03.042 --> 34:05.294
I'm not here for myself.
I'm here for Arthur.

34:05.502 --> 34:07.755
Arthur's path lies with yours.

34:07.838 --> 34:11.132
You have made it clear that
you do not walk in step with me.

34:11.675 --> 34:14.011
You can't want Sigan to win.
You are not evil.

34:14.094 --> 34:16.804
At least Sigan knows
where his loyalties lie.

34:17.389 --> 34:19.516
You have shown that you do not.

34:19.808 --> 34:21.393
So you will let Camelot fall?

34:21.851 --> 34:23.603
| did not say that.

34:24.355 --> 34:25.813
Then you will help me?

34:27.233 --> 34:29.860
To defeat Sigan, you will need a spell

34:29.944 --> 34:33.072
more powerful than anything you know.

34:33.697 --> 34:35.866
Please, I have to try.

34:36.742 --> 34:38.619
Very well,

34:38.702 --> 34:40.788
but you must give me
something in return.

34:41.914 --> 34:43.958
-What?
-A promise.

34:45.376 --> 34:49.588
-A promise?
-That one day you will free me.

34:56.053 --> 34:59.223
If I release you what will you do?

34:59.431 --> 35:01.308
That is not your concern.

35:01.392 --> 35:02.893
| don't trust you.

35:02.977 --> 35:07.523
Nevertheless, you must promise,
or Camelot will fall.

35:08.107 --> 35:10.067
(RUMBLING)

35:12.695 --> 35:14.071
| promise.

35:16.865 --> 35:19.034
Now please, give me the spell.

35:21.453 --> 35:25.791
Close your eyes and open your mind.

35:42.391 --> 35:46.312
Few men have ever been gifted
such knowledge.

35:47.021 --> 35:49.189
Use it wisely.

35:50.566 --> 35:52.526
| will.

35:55.904 --> 35:58.365
You made a promise, young warlock.

35:59.074 --> 36:03.412
And one day I shall keep you to it.

36:11.295 --> 36:13.130
Help! Help!

36:16.467 --> 36:17.676
Arthur!

36:19.595 --> 36:21.263
Arthur!

36:22.264 --> 36:23.599
Retreat!

36:24.683 --> 36:26.352
Regroup in the square.

36:34.443 --> 36:35.736
Arthur!

36:37.696 --> 36:39.490
Arthur!

36:40.991 --> 36:42.284
Arthur!

36:47.748 --> 36:49.792
Save yourselves! That's an order.

36:50.209 --> 36:51.960
Retreat! Retreat!

36:56.799 --> 36:58.384
Seal the doors.

37:01.428 --> 37:03.138
(CREATURE GROWLING)

37:03.222 --> 37:04.807
Where's Arthur?

37:05.724 --> 37:08.352
Where is he?
You can't leave him out there.

37:08.560 --> 37:10.687
-He'll be torn apart.
-You can't go out there, sire!

37:10.771 --> 37:14.358
If you open that door, you will die.
We will all die.

37:14.566 --> 37:15.609
No!

37:15.692 --> 37:17.069
(RUMBLING)

37:27.913 --> 37:29.206
(CHANTING)

37:44.763 --> 37:46.223
(GROANING)

37:50.519 --> 37:52.604
Who would have believed it?

37:53.313 --> 37:55.566
You, a sorcerer.

37:56.900 --> 37:58.610
And a powerful one.

37:59.361 --> 38:01.196
| won't let you hurt him.

38:01.280 --> 38:03.282
And you're going to stop me?

38:07.703 --> 38:09.413
I'll stop you.

38:11.039 --> 38:15.210
He does not deserve your loyalty.
He treats you like a slave.

38:16.086 --> 38:17.504
That's not true.

38:17.588 --> 38:20.466
He cast you aside without
a moment's thought.

38:21.049 --> 38:24.887
-That doesn't matter.
-But it must hurt so much.

38:25.387 --> 38:28.640
To be so put upon, so overlooked,

38:28.724 --> 38:31.393
when all the while you have such power.

38:31.852 --> 38:33.270
That's the way it has to be.

38:33.353 --> 38:34.855
Does it?

38:35.981 --> 38:37.191
You're young, Merlin.

38:37.274 --> 38:41.904
Look inside yourself,
you've yet to discover your true power.

38:42.654 --> 38:44.615
| can help you.

38:47.201 --> 38:52.080
Think, Merlin, to have the world
appreciate your greatness.

38:52.164 --> 38:55.876
To have Arthur know you
for what you are.

38:58.378 --> 39:01.381
-That can never be.
-It can.

39:01.465 --> 39:03.467
If you join me.

39:05.844 --> 39:08.889
Together we can rule over this land.

39:08.972 --> 39:13.435
Arthur will tremble at your voice.
He will kneel at your feet.

39:22.152 --> 39:23.487
| don't want that.

39:24.696 --> 39:26.823
You'd rather be a servant?

39:27.824 --> 39:30.577
Better to serve a good man
than to rule with an evil one.

39:31.036 --> 39:32.371
(INHALES)

39:32.454 --> 39:34.039
So be it.

39:34.623 --> 39:36.792
If you will not join me,

39:36.875 --> 39:38.919
| will become you

39:39.002 --> 39:42.923
and your power will be
harnessed to my will.

39:43.423 --> 39:45.342
(GASPING)

40:09.032 --> 40:11.159
(INDISTINCT WHISPERING)

40:18.083 --> 40:19.793
(CHANTING)

40:45.819 --> 40:47.738
(RAVEN CAWING)

41:06.590 --> 41:07.966
Merlin?

41:40.040 --> 41:41.917
Well done, my boy.

42:00.977 --> 42:03.063
(INDISTINCT WHISPERING)

42:05.357 --> 42:09.027
We must learn our lesson
from these terrible events, Gaius.

42:09.528 --> 42:12.864
-Indeed, sire.
-They prove that I was right.

42:14.700 --> 42:18.745
Magic is evil,
it is our greatest threat.

42:23.041 --> 42:25.085
| have grown complacent, Gaius.

42:27.421 --> 42:29.089
| wouldn't say that, sire.

42:29.464 --> 42:31.299
We must renew our efforts.

42:32.008 --> 42:35.929
We must ensure that all sorcerers
and their followers

42:36.012 --> 42:38.557
are eradicated from this Kingdom.

42:40.934 --> 42:43.228
Of course, sire.

42:49.359 --> 42:51.820
You know you won't
get any thanks, Merlin.

42:51.903 --> 42:52.988
I'm not a complete idiot.

42:55.031 --> 42:57.951
There you go, it's not much,
but you deserve something.

42:58.577 --> 42:59.745
(KNOCK AT DOOR)

43:01.705 --> 43:03.123
I've come to see Merlin.

43:06.042 --> 43:09.504
I've not forgotten about your lazy,
insolent ways.

43:09.588 --> 43:12.799
Or the fact that
you called me a clotpole.

43:13.925 --> 43:16.344
But I do have to admit
that there was some truth

43:16.428 --> 43:18.305
in your accusations against Cedric.

43:20.307 --> 43:22.267
Does this mean you're admitting

43:22.350 --> 43:24.352
that on this occasion
| was actually right?

43:27.397 --> 43:29.191
Not exactly, no.

43:29.274 --> 43:32.736
It means that I have a knighthood
to bestow first thing tomorrow

43:33.653 --> 43:36.114
and no one to clean my armor.

43:36.573 --> 43:38.116
(METAL CLANGING)

43:41.870 --> 43:42.996
All that?

43:43.622 --> 43:44.706
Yep.

43:54.090 --> 43:55.425
Clotpole!

44:05.811 --> 44:08.063
ARTHUR:
What would you know about magic, Merlin?

44:08.146 --> 44:09.272
Nothing.

44:09.356 --> 44:12.651
Today you will fight for glory
and for honor.

44:12.734 --> 44:14.694
That has got to hurt.

44:16.321 --> 44:18.365
ARTHUR:
Nothing could ever happen between us.

44:18.448 --> 44:20.575
When you're king you can change that.

44:20.700 --> 44:23.870
You do realize your wife is a troll.

44:23.954 --> 44:25.163
What?

44:25.247 --> 44:27.749
-(FLATULENCE)
-How could he resist such beauty?

44:28.834 --> 44:30.961
UTHER;:
Send for the witch finder.

44:31.044 --> 44:33.797
Your magic is a secret
to be guarded with your life.

44:35.924 --> 44:38.009
| won't sacrifice a friend
to save myself.

44:38.093 --> 44:40.053
Gaius is already doomed.

44:41.596 --> 44:42.806
My name is Lancelot.

44:45.517 --> 44:46.643
Merlin?

44:49.396 --> 44:52.148
Do not believe that you can lie to me.

44:54.359 --> 44:55.652
They're going to kill each other.

45:07.080 --> 45:08.373
The boy, Merlin.
